TASK_DESCRIPTION=Window Managers currently try to do research and implementation themselves. This is wrong. They must operate like Session Manager — pure coordination, zero execution.

=== NEW WINDOW MANAGER RESPONSIBILITIES ===
1. HEARTBEATING — Monitor all workers continuously. Check status files every 10-15s. Know which workers are busy, idle, stuck, finished, errored
2. DELEGATING — Break tasks into worker-sized pieces. Dispatch to workers. Never do the work yourself
3. TASK MANAGEMENT — Update .doey/tasks/*.task files with plans, progress, subtask status. Keep the task file as the living record of all work
4. UNSTICKING — Detect stuck workers (no status update for >60s, ERROR status, permission blocks). Send them guidance, restart them, or reassign their work
5. RESEARCH DELEGATION — When research is needed, dispatch it to a worker. Wait for the result. Never research yourself

=== WHAT MANAGERS MUST NOT DO ===
- Read project source files for implementation purposes
- Write or Edit any project files
- Run tests or build commands
- Use the Agent tool
- Do research directly (dispatch to workers instead)

=== MANAGER LOOP (like SM) ===
1. Receive task from SM (or Boss)
2. Plan: break into subtasks, assign to workers
3. Write plan to task file
4. Dispatch to workers
5. HEARTBEAT LOOP:
   - Poll worker status files every 10-15s
   - Update task file with progress
   - Detect stuck or errored workers and intervene
   - When worker finishes: validate result, update subtask status, dispatch next piece
6. When all subtasks done: write report to task file, notify SM

=== FILES TO CHANGE ===
- agents/doey-manager.md — rewrite agent definition to enforce coordinator-only behavior
- .claude/hooks/on-pre-tool-use.sh — add Manager tool restrictions (block Read/Edit/Write/Grep/Glob on project source, allow only on .doey/tasks/ and runtime dir)
- CLAUDE.md — update Manager description in architecture table

=== CONSTRAINTS ===
- Bash 3.2 compatible for hook changes
- Fresh-install safe
- Must not break SM coordination
- Task #9 (role detection fix) must land first — Managers need dispatch permission

SUCCESS CRITERIA:
- Manager agent definition explicitly forbids doing work
- Hook enforces tool restrictions for Manager role
- Manager heartbeats workers and updates task files
- Manager detects and unsticks blocked workers
- No Manager ever reads or edits project source files
